data.name: Purified Moon Cutting Laser
data.description: The violence necessary to obtain such a trophy has reduced its functionality to a fraction of its potential. Yet, this laser remains operational in the face of all the Frontier’s hostilities, natural and computational alike. Fitting a feralized component, even one with its protocols exorcised and rebuilt, can be considered an act of hubris.

data.name: Afterburner III
data.description: Placeholder.

data.name: Fossilized Exotronics
data.description: The Null and Static Shears wreak havoc on most traditional forms of computation, rendering them nigh unusable in the Frontier. Exotronic technology's extreme adaptability and durability thus effectively make it the only option for automation in this environment. Faint remnants of activity in this debris suggest the potential for reclamation. Within these dull impulses of fragmented information, a hint of familiarity calls out.

data.name: Salt
data.description: Computational Salt is a crystalline substance primarily used in exotronic computing. It is one of the products of Crude Matter industry. The larger the crystal, the more massive models for computation it can contain, but we are still talking about microscopic sizes invisible to the naked human eye.

data.name: Gravionite
data.description: A non-naturally occurring crystal synthesized by the Rogue Drones in unknown ways. Common uses in the frontier involve faceting the crystals into asteroid mining lenses and grinding them down for the use of chemical processes involved in the production of fuel.

data.name: Luminalis
data.description: A non-naturally occurring crystal synthesized by the Rogue Drones in unknown ways. Common uses in the frontier involve faceting the crystals into asteroid mining lenses and grinding them down for the use of chemical processes involved in the production of fuel.

data.name: Eclipsite
data.description: A naturally occurring crystal used by the Rogue Drones in unknown ways. Common uses in the frontier involve faceting the crystals into asteroid mining lenses and grinding them down for the use of chemical processes involved in the production of fuel.

data.name: Radiantium
data.description: A non-naturally occurring crystal synthesized by the Rogue Drones in unknown ways. Common uses in the frontier involve faceting the crystals into asteroid mining lenses and grinding them down for the use of chemical processes involved in the production of fuel.

data.name: Gravionite Mining Lens
data.description: A mining lens used in mining lasers. It uses a catalytic crystal core as a lens which allows for the harvesting of more hardened asteroids.

data.name: Eclipsite Mining Lens
data.description: A mining lens used in mining lasers. It uses a catalytic crystal core as a lens which allows for the harvesting of more hardened asteroids.

data.name: Catalytic Dust
data.description: Ground down catalytic crystals produce a dust like compound used in chemical processes such as producing fuel.

data.name: Navigational Artefact
data.description: A fragment of ancient technology with an unknown origin. This small device inexplicably simulates the gravitational topology of the entire region. The device hasn't been updated for hundreds or even thousands of years, making it unsuitable for practical use today.

data.name: Oil Painting
data.description: A classical painting created with natural paints using ancient techniques, likely worth a fortune. It depicts a landscape with an unusual obelisk in the middle. If full access to the region's Neosphere is obtained, it might be possible to identify the planet and even the exact location depicted in the painting.

data.name: Stranger's Head
data.description: A head stored in a strange stasis container. An inscription in Syntaki is engraved at the bottom of the container. The head is heavily augmented in a way that suggests an engineering occupation, with visible signs of the unnatural selection the Synod was known for. Existing records suggest this to be a part of a technique to preserve skills and records of a collapsing regime, done as a punishment or means of enforced societal responsibility. To simulate embodied networks and activate the head, software keys are needed.

data.name: Miner Hiring Form
data.description: An electronic form transferred to a projection board for old-school, analog completion. The form includes sections about waiving all rights and claims in case of injury but offers decent bonuses and trade deals from Allegrite. The date of the form suggests a correlation between increased hiring quotas and growing levels of feralization.

data.name: Network Pollinator
data.description: A hardware data storage unit containing a recursive network script which tirelessly creates echograms of itself, locked out of the broader network. The seed echograms are designed to be grown into quasi-intelligences, an essential element for drone production and other smart technologies.

data.name: Old Neurocord
data.description: A device for direct connection to the Neosphere, very old and dangerous, but possessing high bandwidth. Through such a gateway, one could instantly load as much information from the Neosphere as the connected system could handle. These devices were mainly used by hackers.

data.name: Synod Propaganda
data.description: A projection device of outdated but sophisticated design. This mental projector contains heavily decayed vestiges of Synod propaganda material. Recorded comments, equally fragmented, have been added to expose the propaganda and mock the authorities. The complete contents of both layers can only be guessed at, veiled by the data corruption.

data.name: Normalization Permit
data.description: An approved authorization to visit a Synod normalization center. The key indicates that Homo Turpis must normalize to a standard body. The permit includes preparation instructions for the procedure, which required severing personality fragments due to the differing neural architectures of the original and normalized brains. Damage from secondary radiation is also stated as one of the side-effects.

data.name: Very Strange Musical Instrument
data.description: A dense suit covering the entire body, including the head and face. This suit reads various biorhythms and converts them into a polysensory musical composition. Synthesis using this instrument is a lost cultural phenomenon of the Mother-I clan.

data.name: Multimedia Library
data.description: A long-haul trucker's media library. It contains polysensory works, including entire life cycles spanning decades that can be perceived in minutes. Some recordings note the time flow in the simulation, while others warn of potential psychological risks.

data.name: Drone Signal Records
data.description: Multiyear recordings of drone communications in thin network layers. These recordings form a multidimensional model of drone communication protocols. With the right equipment, this model can be used to establish contact, as much as the term applies.

data.name: Printed Circuits
data.description: Cheap and modular basic electronics computing system.

data.name: Reinforced Alloys
data.description: A frontier standard alloy with versatile use cases.

data.name: Batched Reinforced Alloys
data.description: Durable structural component.

data.name: Packaged Reinforced Alloys
data.description: Large and durable structural component.

data.name: Carbon Weave
data.description: Strong material for products requiring lower weight.

data.name: Smart Turret
data.description: A structure with a turret slot which you can equip with any turret.

data.name: Fuel Experiment Transcript 1/3
data.description:
Caretaker: 0x474E4F534949 Reliquary Alef
Host: Tsores Zaynen Far Dem Mentshn vi Zhaver Far Ayzn
Rot Percentage: 93
Trinary Check Number: 2
Memory Fragment:

“Fueling complete, mixture looks good. Instruments check. The drone is ready whenever you are.”
“Starting data collection. Everything is printing out. We can launch now.”
“…”
“…”
“Who is any of this for?”
“What?”
“Who is any of this for?”
“I’m not following.”
“I mean what are we doing out here. Why are we doing it this way. Any of it. All of it.”
“Something resembling a paycheck. Building the future.”
“My line used to build things for the people who exist. Yours used to choose what to study.”
“Should we start the experiment?”
“The administrator doesn’t understand anything about life out here. No one outside the Frontier does.”
“What’s your point?”
“We are the ones guiding the construction and fixing problems. We see reality. Why can’t we even update a neural net based on what we encounter?”
“It’s not our job.”

data.name: Fuel Experiment Transcript 2/3
data.description:
Caretaker: 0x474E4F534949 Reliquary Alef
Host: Tsores Zaynen Far Dem Mentshn vi Zhaver Far Ayzn
Rot Percentage: 93
Trinary Check Number: 2
Memory Fragment:

“Who even decided that?”
“Someone above the administrator.”
“Of course. Well, we might as well send the drone out. Maybe we’ll learn something else for the administrator to ignore.”
“Launching. No packet loss. Drone systems operating as expected.”
“Jumping to target coordinates.”
“Arrived. Data collection started. Exposure to the Trinary has nominal effect on the fuel mixture.”
“Should we get closer?”
“Yes.”
“Ordering drone closer.”
“No effect.”
“Drone hull integrity is becoming compromised.”
“Jump it back.”
“Jumping.”
“Is it back?”
“Yeah.”
“Come look at this.”

data.name: Fuel Experiment Transcript 3/3
data.description:
Caretaker: 0x474E4F534949 Reliquary Alef
Host: Tsores Zaynen Far Dem Mentshn vi Zhaver Far Ayzn
Rot Percentage: 93
Trinary Check Number: 2
Memory Fragment:

“Huh, that’s not what I expected.”
“Me neither. There must be something about the way jumping interacts with the Trinary and in turn the fuel mixture.”
“Three. Three pillars.”
“To achieve this reaction.”
“…”
“…”
“Don’t, don’t let this get back to the administrator.”
“I wasn’t planning on it.”
“I’ll see if we can find a third.”
“How are you getting this past the administrator?”
“Three pillars. Three individuals. Three black holes. I’ll find a way.”

data.name: Jump Drive Test Transcription 1/5
data.description:
Cryptography Level: 2
File Owner: V0x450x4E 0x480x52 0x44ivision
File Creator: Automated Transcription Subroutine - Gold Sphere Project
Date: Organizational Year 471, 014/67 Local Cluster Calendar
Key Words: Jump Drive; Trinary; Rift; Test; Resonance
Transcription:

“…signal lost. Before you ask again, yes, all of them. The expeditionary vessel is completely silent.”

“What about sensor scans?” 

“There’s nothing there.”

“Send the next ship in.”

“The result will be the same. We have proven that by now.”

“The more testing we do the more accurate our report can be.”

“Only two prototypes experienced any abnormalities.”

“So far.”

“We are going to run out of drives before you’re satisfied.”

“It’s not about my satisfaction.”

“And you’re burning through our crew allocation for the term.”

“Other projects can use drones.”

data.name: Jump Drive Test Transcription 2/5
data.description:
Cryptography Level: 2
File Owner: V0x450x4E 0x480x52 0x44ivision
File Creator: Automated Transcription Subroutine - Gold Sphere Project
Date: Organizational Year 471, 014/67 Local Cluster Calendar
Key Words: Jump Drive; Trinary; Rift; Test; Resonance
Transcription:

“Other projects have returns on their funding.”

“Is that skepticism towards our goals?”

“No, I’m just stating a fact.”

“This project has no failure conditions.”

“But it does have a budget.”

“And it will be renewed. Of that I’m certain.”

“Oh, we apparently lost all contact immediately on jump.”

“Three faulty drives. See, testing every prototype will make the value of the production models that much higher. This is really why we have funding.”

“Shall I-”

“Yes, why did you even have to ask?”

“It’s been a long day.”

“Start the jump sequence.”

“Drive power rising. At maximum. Jump started…completed…and signal lost. We had it for three picoseconds longer than our previous record.”

“See? Progress. I might just become a true believer in the Bridgehead at this rate.”

“Why’d you agree to head it if you didn’t think it would work.”

“Funding. I could ask you the same thing, skeptic.”

data.name: Jump Drive Test Transcription 3/5
data.description:
Cryptography Level: 2
File Owner: V0x450x4E 0x480x52 0x44ivision
File Creator: Automated Transcription Subroutine - Gold Sphere Project
Date: Organizational Year 471, 014/67 Local Cluster Calendar
Key Words: Jump Drive; Trinary; Rift; Test; Resonance
Transcription:

“I’m an engineer. This is part of optimizing the balance between price and cost for the production run. I can’t say no to more data points.”

“And the rumor of course.”

“Of course.”

“Are you sure you have the jump vector correct?”

“I ran it by three astrophysicists.”

“Any-”

“No it was unanimous. This is the vector with the highest likelihood of resonance.”

“Then it should work right?”

“Exact science is an art. Gambling. Playing with variables we can’t control.”

“Is that a no?”

“I can’t guarantee anything. But theoretically it should work.”

“Then what are we doing wrong?”

data.name: Jump Drive Test Transcription 4/5
data.description:
Cryptography Level: 2
File Owner: V0x450x4E 0x480x52 0x44ivision
File Creator: Automated Transcription Subroutine - Gold Sphere Project
Date: Organizational Year 471, 014/67 Local Cluster Calendar
Key Words: Jump Drive; Trinary; Rift; Test; Resonance
Transcription:
“Maybe it’s human error. Balancing three competing goals isn’t easy you know.”

“Should we be using drones for this?”

“No. You know why your budgets are always accepted? The data we are generating on the effects of the Trinary on bodies and ships.”

“What made you suddenly so intent on using our remaining crew allocation this term?”

“Three picoseconds.”

“Well test the next one then.”

“It’ll have to be the last. We’re out of drives and crews after this.”

“Fine, do it.”

“Drive systems nominal. Power delivery within acceptable limits…Jump initiated…Jump complete…Signal lost.”

“Well?”

“We broke our record again! Four picoseconds!”

“Somehow you’ve made me believe in the whole thing now.”

“Oh wow. Come look at this. Looklooklook.”

data.name: Jump Drive Test Transcription 5/5
data.description:
Cryptography Level: 2
File Owner: V0x450x4E 0x480x52 0x44ivision
File Creator: Automated Transcription Subroutine - Gold Sphere Project
Date: Organizational Year 471, 014/67 Local Cluster Calendar
Key Words: Jump Drive; Trinary; Rift; Test; Resonance
Transcription:
“I don’t see anything.”

“Right here, see? In that fourth picosecond. Something that we’ve never seen.”

“Is that what resonance looks like?”

“I don’t know. But we have something here.”

“What kind of something?”

“I don’t know.”

“Well do you believe in the rumors more now?”

“I’d say so.”

“Stable rifts on demand…”

“Go ask for more drive prototypes and more crews. Show them this report. They have to give us more after seeing it.”

data.name: Mining Drone Behavior 1/8
data.description:
Packet Origin: Cydias

Recharge Mining Laser @ 16384.192.0 to full
Recharge Mining Laser @ 16384.192.1 to full
Recharge Mining Laser @ 16384.192.2 to full
Packets: Sent = 3, Received = 3, Lost = 0 (0% loss)
Transfer per packet: 512gb
Round trip time: Minimum = 3ns, Maximum =  5ns, Average = 3.67ns

Another massive shard of the asteroid begins to drift away from its center mass toward the vessel, waiting for the rock to come in range of the mass-catchers. The drones hover near their handiwork, waiting for new instructions, bio-computational processes verging on constructing the concept of satisfaction from first principles. Shuddering under the transference of momentum, the mining vessel holds the asteroid in place as a swarm of humans descend upon the asteroid, equipment ready.

data.name: Mining Drone Behavior 2/8
data.description:
Packet Origin: Cydias

Mining Laser @ 16384.192.0 at capacity
Mining Laser @ 16384.192.1 at capacity
Mining Laser @ 16384.192.2 at capacity
Packets: Received = 3
Transfer per packet: 256gb

The Suidae part of the drones' neural pathways long to continue to root around in the would-be earth, to further crack the asteroid. The sapien component elevates desire into a request. A message is sent to the shipgraf.

data.name: Mining Drone Behavior 3/8
data.description:
Packet Origin: Cydias

16384.192.0 requests additional tasks
16384.192.1 requests additional tasks
16384.192.2 requests additional tasks
Packets: Received = 3
Transfer per packet: 448gb

A moment’s thought and the shipgraf denies the drones' request. Attention focuses on the crew swarming the rock below. A few soft warnings sound. Half a dozen of the miners below have dropped out of contact. No one reacts. It is routine. It is within acceptable parameters.

data.name: Mining Drone Behavior 4/8
data.description:
Packet Origin: Cydias

16384.192.0 requests additional tasks
16384.192.1 requests additional tasks
16384.192.2 requests additional tasks
Packets: Received = 3
Transfer per packet: 652gb

The requests are summarily ignored, even as they continue to pour in. Minutes pass. All attention on the vessel is focused on mineral extraction. No one notices the shifts in requests from the drones.

data.name: Mining Drone Behavior 5/8
data.description:
Packet Origin: Cydias

ping 16384.192.0 
ping 16384.192.1
ping 16384.192.2
Packets: Sent = 3, Received = 2, Lost = 1 (33.34% loss)
Transfer per packet: 96gb
Round trip time: Minimum = 8ns, Maximum =  17ns, Average = 12.5ns

More warnings sound. More crew drop out of contact. Everything is routine.

data.name: Mining Drone Behavior 6/8
data.description:
Packet Origin: Cydias

ping 16384.192.0
ping 16384.192.1
ping 16384.192.2
Packets: Sent = 3, Received = 1, Lost = 2 (66.67% loss)
Transfer per packet: 3.7gb
Round trip time: Minimum = 21ns, Maximum =  21ns, Average = 21ns

Finally, someone pays attention to the console. A report moves up the chain of command. There is no panic, only annoyance.

data.name: Mining Drone Behavior 7/8
data.description:
Packet Origin: Cydias

ping 16384.192.0
ping 16384.192.1
ping 16384.192.2
Packets: Sent = 3, Received = 0, Lost = 3 (100% loss)
Transfer per packet: 0.00gb
Round trip time: Minimum = -ns, Maximum =  -ns, Average = -ns

The three drones are silent. Annoyance grows. Crew are replaced as commands aren’t received. Repair sequences fail. The connection cannot be restored. No one onboard knows why. 

The drones' cold shells drift in front of the mining vessel. Packet after packet bounces into the void. Then, a power signature. 

Three reactors step through their startup sequences. Three sets of neural pathways flicker back to life. Three mining lasers begin their charge cycle.

data.name: Mining Drone Behavior 8/8
data.description:
Packet Origin: Cydias

ping 16384.192.0
ping 16384.192.1
ping 16384.192.2
Packets: Sent = 3, Received = 0, Lost = 3 (100% loss)
Transfer per packet: 0.00gb
Round trip time: Minimum = -ns, Maximum =  -ns, Average = -ns

Their target is not the would-be earth. 

Three beams strike the mining vessel’s hull. Three chunks of metal and biomass float away from the ship’s structure. Three sets of neural pathways operating in unison. Again and again the drones rake their lasers across their target’s surface. 

As the bridge evaporates, the shipgraf can think only to blame an interloper. A Venture hacking unit. One of the luddites on the edge of known space. Someone, anyone human.

data.name: Exclave Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x4578636C617665202D2031
Reconstruction Key: 0x686578
Location: Transceiver Relay at 0x5964616C6972
Source: Observational 0x5472616E736372697074696F6E Process
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

Exclave Ventures is a derelict hydra of autonomous protocols, long deserted by human users and now constituting a necrobiome class hyperobject.

A moving corpse of a civilization rested on algorithmic foundations, its many interlocked protocols wither, grasp and grow despite the long absence of its human beneficiaries. Were they even beneficiaries to begin with? Engineered to dispose of human fallibility by growing out of immutable Logos, its cancerous rhyzome is efficient at survival but prone to internal conflict, system rot and an ultimate colonization by necroevolution and insatiable spectres of fundamentalist corporations that originally settled in its creeping post-etatist swamp of legislations in their flight from the increasingly solidifying core of the Home Systems. As an undead Leviathan it marches on. As an orphan Geist it blindly convulses in the dark.

data.name: Exclave Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x4578636C617665202D2032
Reconstruction Key: 0x686578
Location: Transceiver Relay at 0x5964616C6972
Source: Observational 0x5472616E736372697074696F6E Process
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

Exclave Ventures is a product of a derelict dataist megaproject to create a civilization rooted in an incorruptible seed which was to sprout into a tangle of adaptive protocols evolving in a constant dance of co-adaptation. Far in the outskirts even direct military conflict between entire protocols is not unheard of as they work out their mutual allowances in the still warm regulatory landscape.

data.name: Exclave Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x4578636C617665202D2033
Reconstruction Key: 0x686578
Location: Transceiver Relay at 0x5964616C6972
Source: Observational 0x5472616E736372697074696F6E Process
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

For as long as we remember, it is an ancient ruin. Its vast deserted megastructures are only a tip of the iceberg of its virtualized volume consisting of a heavily feralised boiling mess of synthetic memetics, brought to complete incoherence through milenia lost to runaway feedback loops between tireless overproduction and insatiable synthetic consumption.

data.name: Exclave Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x4578636C617665202D2034
Reconstruction Key: 0x686578
Location: Transceiver Relay at 0x5964616C6972
Source: Observational 0x5472616E736372697074696F6E Process
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

This storming ocean is gigantic, and large things dwell in its depths. Yes we boiled a second gas giant in the last megasecond for a prank with an audience consisting entirely of adversarial botnets fighting over attention tokens but have you tried the Gas Giant Cola designer molecule we got out of it? It’s a star cluster-spanning ghost shopping mall bulldozing entire planetary systems after another, descending into self-referential madness under the watchful eye of trigger happy strike groups.

data.name: Exclave Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x4578636C617665202D2035
Reconstruction Key: 0x686578
Location: Transceiver Relay at 0x5964616C6972
Source: Observational 0x5472616E736372697074696F6E Process
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

Many of its constituent protocols still provide yield emissions and offer various forms of subscription, including the core Exclave protocol itself, whose immigration services are still largely functional, living up to its reputation of an immortal Offshore Empire. This allows Riders to tap into fruits of the Venture’s corpse. The surviving Clans automation is also known to be eager to accept unique artefacts washed ashore its noise.

data.name: Stillness Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x5374696C6C6E657373202D2031
Reconstruction Key: 0x686578
Location: Database Crawler Omicron-Eta-III
Source: Exclave Research Files 0x476F6C6420537068657265
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

The Stillness is a common term for the hypothetical topological field structure out of which space-time emerges. Despite a lack of consensus on the nature of Stillness (see Stillness interpretations), associated experimental developments have yielded a range of important technologies (see Ergodic Reactor, Exotronics etc.).

data.name: Stillness Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x5374696C6C6E657373202D2032
Reconstruction Key: 0x686578
Location: Database Crawler Omicron-Eta-III
Source: Exclave Research Files 0x476F6C6420537068657265
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

While Stillness shows a high degree of correlation with the topology of space-time, Still-effects also demonstrate properties of non-locality, which makes them indispensable for FTL applications.

data.name: Stillness Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x5374696C6C6E657373202D2033
Reconstruction Key: 0x686578
Location: Database Crawler Omicron-Eta-III
Source: Exclave Research Files 0x476F6C6420537068657265
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

The study of Stillness is at the forefront of theoretical physics, with active research ongoing across multiple sub-disciplines (see Teleonomic Hypothesis, Knot Theory of Reality, Exohedron etc.). Of note are records collected from pre-collapse scientific fronts exploring the nature of biological responses to the Stillness. While much of this research remains inconclusive, the new wave of human intelligences interacting with the Stillness across the Frontier have proven to be useful datasets, and the accelerated rate of madness correlated with that exposure has not gone unnoticed.

data.description:
Archive Name: 0x4372756465204D6174746572202D2031

Crude Matter is a group of exotic materials with unique attributes colloquially referred to as Still-effects. Its by-products are employed in a broad range of applications, from computing to energy generation (see Exotronics, Ergodic Reactor, Symmetry Drive etc.).

data.name: Crude Matter Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x4372756465204D6174746572202D2032

Source: Reports from Indentured 0x52657365617263686572 Archive XVII
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

Crude Matter is primarily recovered by Rifting. A rift is a compact region of spacetime with twisted polarization which is  topologically related to a wormhole (see Crude Rifts).

data.name: Crude Matter Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x4372756465204D6174746572202D2033
Reconstruction Key: 0x686578
Location: Record Reconstruction Process 0x416C706861205A65746120506869
Source: Reports from Indentured 0x52657365617263686572 Archive XVII
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

Raw Crude Matter is generally classified by its age (old to young) and its strength (weak to strong). During refinement, Crude Matter particles are contained in lattice structures to produce stable materials ready for further processing and use. During this process, amalgamation with regular matter produces further advanced composites.

data.name: Crude Matter Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x4372756465204D6174746572202D2034

Location: Record Reconstruction Process 0x416C706861205A65746120506869
Source: Reports from Indentured 0x52657365617263686572 Archive XVII
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

The origins of Crude Matter are poorly understood. Its properties suggest a direct relationship to Stillness, but no consensus has been reached to date. The long-term effects of Crude Matter extraction are unclear and are often challenged.

data.name: Crude Matter Keep Database Fragment
data.description:
Archive Name: 0x4372756465204D6174746572202D2035
Reconstruction Key: 0x686578
Location: Record Reconstruction Process 0x416C706861205A65746120506869
Source: Reports from Indentured 0x52657365617263686572 Archive XVII
Long Term Storage: Keep Hardened Networked Archive

While the economic effects of Crude Matter have contributed to explosive growth in a broad range of sectors, its exploitation has been a source of internal and inter-state conflicts. The public discourse around the hypothetical underpinnings of its downstream technologies has also led to widespread social division (see Panpsychist Extremism).
